GDB:

GDB or the Gnu Debugger is a debugger for linux binaries.

Installation:

sudo apt install gdb

Usage:

set disassembly-flavor intel | set disassembled language to intel
break *<address> | sets breakpoint at address
break <function> | sets breakpoint at function
info functions | list all functions of the binary
info registers | prints all the registers to the screen
info frame | print current stack frame
si | step one instruction
ni | step one instruction without following a call
